# Phase 6 — Build Log

**Goal:** Personalization layer for "Find My Stack" — per-tool AI Reports with scraped sentiment (Reddit, X, Quora, G2), 5 pros / 5 cons, pricing analysis, community buzz, learning curve, integration fit, and plan-page enrichment (sentiment badges + quick verdicts).

**Design decisions:**
- (D) Light enrichment on plan page + deep-dive report page
- (C) Hybrid scrape-on-first-request, cached with 7-day TTL
- (B) AI-synthesized insights (not verbatim quotes)
- All 10 report sections

---

## Step 6.1 — Database schema
**Status:** ✅ Completed
**Jira:** KAN-7
**File:** `supabase/migrations/035_tool_sentiment_cache.sql`

Created `tool_sentiment_cache` table with columns for all 10 report sections (ai_verdict, pros, cons, sentiment_score, sentiment_breakdown, themes, best_for, not_for, pricing_analysis, community_buzz, learning_curve, integration_insights), raw scraped data (raw_reddit, raw_twitter, raw_quora, raw_g2), metadata (mention_count, sources_scraped, status, scraped_at, synthesized_at, expires_at). UNIQUE(tool_id), indexes on tool_id / expires_at / status, RLS policies (public read, service-role write).

Migration was run manually in Supabase SQL Editor (confirmed by user).

