## Step 6.8 — Testing & polish
**Status:** ✅ Completed
**Jira:** KAN-14

### Type check & build
- `npx tsc --noEmit` → 0 errors
- `npx next build` → ✅ compiled successfully, all routes emitted, including:
  - `ƒ /tools/[slug]/report`
  - `ƒ /api/tools/[slug]/report`
  - `ƒ /api/tools/[slug]/report/generate`
  - `ƒ /api/tools/[slug]/report/status`
  - `ƒ /api/cron/scrape-sentiment`
  - `ƒ /api/plan` (enriched)

### Build-time fixes
During `next build` the untyped Supabase admin client produced `never`-type errors on the new `tool_sentiment_cache` table (it isn't in any generated `Database` types). Fixed by casting the admin/supabase clients to `any` inside the cron and generate routes so the `.upsert()` / `.select()` calls type-check. Also coerced nullable `CronTool` fields (`skill_level`, `features`, `integrations`, `platforms`) to the non-null shape `synthesizeReport` expects when batching the cron.

### Known runtime prerequisites
- `APIFY_API_TOKEN` env var must be set for Twitter / Quora / G2 scrapers
- `CRON_SECRET` env var must be set for the cron endpoint
- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` already configured (used by existing `/api/plan`)

### Flow validated
- Homepage CTA → `/plan?q=...` now auto-submits (bug from last session fixed)
- Category search falling back to keyword search when a category has no matches
- Plan tool cards render sentiment badge + quick verdict + "See full report →" link when cache exists
- Report page polling state machine handles all four states (loading / generating / ready / failed)

